    "David Blitzer runs the tactical opportunities group at alternative investment giant Blackstone.",
    "In 2011, he joined forces with Apollo Global's Joshua Harris to buy the NBA's Philadelphia 76ers.",
    "Blitzer and Harris later added the NHL's New Jersey Devils, English soccer club Crystal Palace and a small stake in the NFL's Pittsburgh Steelers to their holdings.",
    "Blitzer also owns a stake in MLB's Cleveland Guardians, and he co-owns MLS's Real Salt Lake alongside Qualtrics cofounder Ryan Smith."
